@zSeriesGuy Hey there, that's a nice suggestion, thank you!

But because we are working on Sermon Manager Pro in the background, we are going to have to say "no" for that feature, since customization will be one of the big selling points of it, and we already have something similar implemented for it, so it just would not be wise to add the same feature to the free version of Sermon Manager.

I hope that you understand our view, and I hope that this doesn't discourage you from suggesting more features or improvements for it.

@robertmain I already have most of our preachers as authors, they also write blog posts. So using the already established method for attributing WordPress content would allow me to keep all our Ministers content on one Author page too.

@nikola3244 I don't need Sermon Manager to do anything different on the front end, just have the option that it does not hide the already existing Author Picker on the back end. 

Being able to see the WordPress Author picker when creating a new sermon would allow me to choose anything other than my own details to be associated with the sermon and would be a better solution than the current implimentstion.

User replied back with his official rewrite/code

```
// Display all series or speakers in a grid of images
function wpfc_display_images_shortcode( $atts = array () ) {
extract( shortcode_atts( array(
'tax' => 'wpfc_sermon_series', // options: wpfc_sermon_series, wpfc_preacher, wpfc_sermon_topics
'order' => 'DESC', // options: ASC, DESC
'orderby' => 'id', // options: id, count, name, slug, term_group, none
'size' => 'sermon_medium', // options: any size registered with add_image_size
'show_desc' => 'false',
'max_items' => 0
), $atts ) );

$terms = apply_filters( 'sermon-images-get-terms', '', array('taxonomy' => $tax, 'term_args' => array('order' => $order, 'orderby' => $orderby, 'number' => $max_items) ) );
if ( ! empty( $terms ) ) {
$list = '<ul id="wpfc_images_grid">'; foreach( (array) $terms as $term ) {
$list .= '<li class="wpfc_grid_image">';
$list .= '<a href="' . esc_url( get_term_link( $term, $term->taxonomy ) ) . '">' . wp_get_attachment_image( $term->image_id, $size ) . '</a>';
$list .= '<h3 class="wpfc_grid_title"><a href="' . esc_url( get_term_link( $term, $term->taxonomy ) ) . '">' . $term->name . '</a></h3>';
if ( $show_desc == 'true' ) {
if ( ! empty( $term->description ) ) {
$list .= '<div class="taxonomy-description">' . $term->description . '</div>';
}
}
$list .= '</li>';
}
$list .= '</ul>';
}
return $list;
}
```
